library(tidyverse)     # for graphing and data cleaning
library(lubridate)     # for date manipulation
library(ggthemes)      # for even more plotting themes
theme_set(theme_minimal()) # My favorite ggplot() theme :)

Data choice 2: Alternative fuel stations

stations <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2022/2022-03-01/stations.csv')

Read more about the Alternative fuel stations data, including definitions of variables, here.

library(tidyverse)     # for data cleaning and plotting
library(gardenR)       # for Lisa's garden data
library(lubridate)     # for date manipulation
library(openintro)     # for the abbr2state() function
library(palmerpenguins)# for Palmer penguin data
library(maps)          # for map data
library(ggmap)         # for mapping points on maps
library(gplots)        # for col2hex() function
library(RColorBrewer)  # for color palettes
library(sf)            # for working with spatial data
library(leaflet)       # for highly customizable mapping
library(ggthemes)      # for more themes (including theme_map())
theme_set(theme_minimal())
stationsPA <- stations %>% 
  filter(STATE == "PA") 
PA <- get_stamenmap(
  bbox = c(left = -80.586, bottom = 39.550, right = -74.598, top = 42.318), 
  maptype = "toner",
  zoom = 7)

ggmap(PA) +
  geom_point(data = stationsPA, 
             aes(x = X, y = Y), 
             color = "navyblue",
             alpha = 1, 
             size = 1) +
  labs(title = "Alternative Fuel Stations in PA", caption = "Made by Brant Newman") +
  theme_map()
